comments.body:
Thanks for your help Ashraf!

I'm not using Titanium Studio so not sure what I need to modify. I already have
{code}
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE"/>
{code}
in my tiapp.xmp

The fix for this is to actually specify the write permission for external storage within the tiapp.xml.

{code}
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
{code}

Also, per the Android documentation, reading from external storage will also require a permission tag as well. 

{code}
<uses-permission android:name="android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE" />
{code}

This is documented here:
http://developer.android.com/training/basics/data-storage/files.html

Adding the Camera privilege can work since it requires storage access, but isn't necessary. Using the above works just fine.
